AUSTRALIAN OPEN
January 27, 2004
Sebastien Grosjean
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 
THE MODERATOR:  Questions, please.  
 
 
Q.  Was it something that happened in the match? 
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  Yeah.  Yeah, yeah. 
 
Q.  What happened and when? 
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  Was more when I play a forehand, he play straight to my forehand, and I felt something really hard in my leg straightaway.  It was tough after to move, so I couldn't really move and give 100 percent on the court.  You know, it happen in the last year as well, and I keep playing, and after I stop eight weeks.  So, you know, I really felt the same thing, so that's why I stopped. 
 
Q.  Is it the groin, the top of the leg?
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  Yes, yes.  At the top of the leg, yes. 
 
Q.  On the right-hand side?
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  On the right side.  
 
Q.  What game was it? 
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  It was the game on the -- to do 3-love.  
 
Q.  Is it something that you might have to even have surgery on? 
 
SEBASTIEN GROSJEAN:  I don't hope so, but I have to do MRI first to see.  We do tomorrow MRI and I will see what is it.   
 

